description:
This a local Indivisible event!
Protest to Support our LGBTQ+ Community

Date: Sunday, June 22nd 
Time: 4:00PM-5:30PM
Location: Hyannis Airport Rotary (details about parking and where exactly to stand listed below.)

description:
We are going to be at Erie Pride and we need your help!  Please sign up to volunteer with us at our table.  Talk to your community, have fun and learn more about One Colorado.  

We’re thrilled to share that One Colorado will be attending 12 Pride events across the state this summer with even more on the calendar for this coming fall. From the Eastern Plains, through the Front Range, and to the Western Slope, we’re traveling far and wide to connect with LGBTQIA+ Coloradans and their families!

At each stop, we’ll be sharing what we’ve been up to from health equity and safe schools to voter engagement and trans rights. We also want to hear from you! Your stories, your needs, and your voices help shape the work we do every day.

But let’s also remember that Pride began as a riot, a powerful act of resistance led by trans women of color, fighting back against police brutality and demanding dignity and justice. Pride is a celebration, of course, but it’s also a call to action!

Join MomsRising and Advancement Project for a VIRTUAL Teach-In on Supporting Immigrant Students and Families in Hostile School Environments. 

In today’s polarized political climate, supporting immigrant students in public schools is more critical than ever. As national debates around immigration grow increasingly heated, schools, which should be sanctuaries of learning and belonging, can unintentionally mirror the hostility, fear, and discrimination seen in broader society. Without intentional collective efforts to support immigrant students and families, bias, harmful policies and practices, and a lack of cultural understanding can create environments where immigrant students feel unsafe, unseen, and excluded. Left unchecked, these hostile conditions not only harm students’ academic achievement and mental health but also weaken the fabric of school communities.

It will take all of us actively fostering inclusive, affirming spaces, in our schools and communities to counteract division, uphold the principles of dignity and opportunity, and ensure that every student, regardless of birthplace or status, has the chance to thrive, lead, and contribute to a stronger, more equitable future for us all because to be honest we are better together.

title: NO KINGS St. Louis County
description:
In America, we don’t put up with would-be kings. NO KINGS is a national day of action and mass mobilization in response to increasing authoritarian excesses and corruption from Trump and his allies. We’ve watched as they’ve cracked down on free speech, detained people for their political views, threatened to deport American citizens, and defied the courts. They’ve done this all while continuing to serve and enrich their billionaire allies.

🚨On Saturday, June 14, we’re taking to the streets nationwide. We’re not gathering to feed his ego. We’re building a movement that leaves him behind.🚨

The flag doesn’t belong to Donald Trump. It belongs to us. We’re not watching history happen. We’re making it.

On June 14th, we’re showing up everywhere he isn’t—to say no thrones, no crowns, no kings. Check out nokings.org for more information.

Join us in Ballwin, MO for a national day of protest. Bring your signs and your energy, and let's remind the Trump Administration that there are no kings in America.

This will be a peaceful, nonviolent protest. Families are welcome!

Time: 11:30AM-1:30PM

Location: Manchester Road in Ballwin (Manchester and Weidman, although check back for the final location)

Please, for your own safety, stay out of the roads during all protests. This protects you and our movement.

This is an outdoor event, and we value your safety. In the event of dangerous weather, we reserve the right to cancel this event. Please check the Mobilize website two hours prior to the event to ensure that the event is proceeding as planned.

A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.

address_lines: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
location.venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details

description:
Whether you're looking for ways to have better conversations with family and friends, or you're writing your own political blog, framing issues that are important to you can sometimes be difficult. We'll have trainers from Faith in Minnesota share effective messaging basics to keep in mind using the Race Class Gender Narrative techniques. 

Race Class Gender Narrative is equal parts empirically-tested messaging, organizing strategy, and creative communications approach fused together to motivate and mobilize people to reject faux populism, fear- and dog whistle-based messaging and embrace progressive solutions and the kind of policies and government that can implement them. This training will teach you:

– What is Race Class Gender Narrative and why we should use it.

– How to create winning messages.

– Share research-based messaging that meets our current moment.

Indivisible groups in Minnesota have incorporated these skills and offered these trainings for years to help improve communications around issues that can be tough. It will change how you approach conversations both online and in-person with friends and neighbors.

This event is in-person only, and will not be recorded.
